                     <interp inst="t18221023-72-person807" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 28th of September, my shift hung in the yard to dry - I missed it next morning. The prisoner was my <rs id="t18221023-72-deflabel392" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-72-defend803 t18221023-72-deflabel392"></join>, and had the care of it, as I was ill. On the 6th of October, I found it on her person, made into a petticoat - I know it by the gores which I cut. I charged her with stealing it; she said I had better swear it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221023-72-person808">
                  MARY 
                  ANN BATE
               <interp inst="t18221023-72-person808" type="surname" value="ANN BATE"></interp>
